I went here last night to celebrate my friend’s birthday and as soon as we got to the door we were informed by security that they were closed and not letting anyone else in. That’s fine, it was only 11:30 so I was confused as to why online said they closed at 2am. The “manger” comes to the door and says “blame his network guy he’s been trying to contact him for weeks” I then asked him for his information because I had driven 45mins to come to this spot after hearing good things about it. He refused to give me his name and then walked off while I was talking to him. That is where I felt disrespected! Looks over and completely disregarded to a first time customer. He then went inside and started yelling “alright everybody out!! Let’s go! We’re closed!” Just rude!!! I will NEVER go again and will make sure the people who once spoke so highly of this place hears about my unfortunate first impression.

i’ve been coming to this bar for a good year now. i started working in the neighborhood last summer so i decided to give it a try. since then, i’ve been treated nicely each visit. just about everyone is really friendly/cool to chat with, honestly.  it’s unfortunate that i JUST had their food for the first time this spring & man, is it good! their angus burger is super good & filling.  their mac & cheese is also really good. my favorite for sure! + prices are reasonable for what you get it so i have no issue there. i recommend this place for sure if you’re in the area for a brew & good food!  (PS: if you work in the neighborhood, they offer a neighborhood discount!!)

Definitely a great place for house heads on a Thursday night out.  This bar is definitely moving up in the local scene as it has great ambiance and friendly staff. I do my best to stop by in Thursday nights and the music is quite good if you are into house/dance music. The only criticism I would relay is the bathroom is small. Other than that the seating is ample and the bar is well stocked. They have a pool table and a small space for dancing. Parking is an OK situation as it is on the street and is public. I suggest taking your favorite rideshare and bringing some like minded house enthusiasts. I would say it is definitely worth a visit.  Also tell them Gerard sent you.
